Within this course an understanding of the role of the practitioner of applied theatre and self-understanding in this role is gained. The principles of group dynamics, giving feedback and importance of starting from developmental psychology when planning the applied theatre process are discussed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide an overview and understanding of the role of an applied theater practitioner.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Understands the principles of group management in applied theatre. Understands the principles of working with the personal stories of participants in the applied theatre process. Understands how developmental psychology is an important factor when planning the applied theatre process. Understands her/his role as an applied theatre facilitator.
